    public interface HasEvidences
    The superclass of all annotation items in a UniProtEntry, which can be tagged with evidence tags.

    These values can be found in the many lines of the flat file. Some examples are marked in the following example. Note that more than one evidence tag can be added to an evidence tagable class. 
     ...
 ID   Q8J030      PRELIMINARY;      PRT;   669 AA.
 AC   Q8J030;
 DT   01-MAR-2003 (TrEMBLrel. 23, Created)
 DT   01-MAR-2003 (TrEMBLrel. 23, Last sequence update)
 DT   01-MAR-2003 (TrEMBLrel. 23, Last annotation update)
 DE   Galactosylceramidase (Krabbe disease){EI1,EP2}.
 OS   Homo sapiens (Human).
 OC   Eukaryota; Metazoa; Chordata; Craniata; Vertebrata; Euteleostomi;
 OC   Mammalia; Eutheria; Primates; Catarrhini; Hominidae; Homo.
 OX   NCBI_TaxID=9606{EP2};
 RN   [1]{EI1}
 RP   SEQUENCE FROM N.A.
 RC   TISSUE=Testis;
 RA   Strausberg R.;
 RL   Submitted (AUG-2002) to the EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ databases.
 DR   EMBL; BC036518; AAH36518.1; -.{EI1}
 ...
    In XML: 
     ...
 <entry dataset="TrEMBL" created="1998-01-01" modified="2005-02-01">
 <accession>O22222</accession>
 <name>O22222_ARATH</name>
 <protein evidence="EP3">
 <name>Hypothetical protein At2g41600</name>
 <name>At2g41600/T32G6.12</name>
 </protein>
 <gene>
 <name type="primary" evidence="EI1,EP3">At2g41600</name>
 </gene>
 <organism key="1">
 <name type="scientific">Arabidopsis thaliana</name>
 <name type="common">Mouse-ear cress</name>
 <dbReference type="NCBI Taxonomy" id="3702" evidence="EI1" key="2"/>
 ...
 </organism>
 <reference evidence="EI1" key="3">
 <citation type="submission" date="2000-03" db="EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ databases">
 ...
 </citation>
 <scope>NUCLEOTIDE SEQUENCE.</scope>
 </reference>

 </dbReference>
